# @dna-decompose

Mechanical validator for parallel task decomposition. Runs between `/speckit-tasks` and `@dna-delegate`.

## What it does

Parses `specs/NNN-*/tasks.md` for tasks marked `[P]`. For each `[P]` group in a phase, verifies no two tasks touch the same file. Collisions would cause merge conflicts the moment parallel implementer dispatches write back.

## How to invoke

```
bash .cursor/scripts/dna-decompose/run.sh specs/NNN-feature-name
```

PASS. safe to decompose and run parallel implementations (see `@dna-delegate`).
FAIL. two or more `[P]` tasks claim overlapping files. Either serialize them (remove the `[P]` marker from one), or split the file touches more granularly.

## Common failures

- Two `[P]` tasks both editing the same model file. Solution: serialize, or add an intermediate `[P]` task that shapes the shared interface first, then the two downstream tasks can genuinely be parallel.
- A `[P]` task claims a module path (e.g., `src/models/`) that another `[P]` task lists a specific file within. Decompose's glob-intersection check flags this.

## Refuses

Cannot be overridden. Parallel tasks with file-overlap WILL produce conflicts. The gate exists to prevent the conflict at spec-time, not resolve it at merge-time.
